{
  "texts": [
    "There are two general types of bias that can be introduced in a human-computer system, over-reliance, and under-reliance.",
    "Overreliance, also known as automation bias increases the risk of False Positive (FP) and False Negative (FN) results: if the AI is right most of the time, radiologists may stop verifying the outputs, or come to trust the AI more than their own judgment.",
    "In this scenario the radiologist will accept incorrect AI results.",
    "Underreliance has the same effect for the opposite reason.",
    "If the radiologist does not trust the AI results, they may disregard accurate AI output, also increasing FP and FN results."
  ]
}